"In our era and in our cultural context marked by the impact of technology and the lifestyle that springs from it - said&nbsp; Fr. Marco Moroni, OFMConv, Custos of the Sacred Convent >-, is very significant the growing trend of slow tourism and pilgrimage on foot, as an opportunity to return to the essential. And the search for the essential, > from which world is world, is the first step of every authentic spiritual journey. Saint Francis, the man who was Pellegrino in the fields, in the villages and castles of his time to invite men and women to focus their lives around him and to what does not pass and does not “arrugginisce”, continues to invite so many people - also through slow tourism - to carry out this itinerary, which while physical, is at the same time internal. And we his sons and disciples are happy and honored to be able to welcome, support and value those who have this courage and set themselves on their way."
