AGI - Pope Francis is without fever and continues the therapy remodulated after examinations and investigations that have shown "a complex clinical picture" due to "a polymicrobial infection of the respiratory tract". Its decency on the tenth floor of the Gemelli > Hospital is long and, as the Vatican press, "adequate".
<
Francesco's mood - admitted from last Friday - is "good" has emphasized the director of the press room Matteo Bruni.
The night spent "was quiet", > "has rested well", "has made breakfast".&nbsp;"This morning - the last update of the Vatican press room - has received the Eucharist and subsequently has dedicated itself to
some working activities and reading of texts.' In addition, Francis, "touched by the numerous messages of affection and closeness that continues to receive in these hours" wished to address "your thanks to those who are now admitted to the hospital, for the affection and love that express through the drawings and the greeting messages", "pray for them and asks that you pray for him".
</div
But what is a polymicrobial infection in the lungs? It is a lung pathology caused by the simultaneous presence of more than one pathogen microorganism, such as bacteria, viruses, fungi or other infectious agents. These microorganisms can interact with each other, enhancing their virulence and making the diagnosis and treatment of infection more complex.&nbsp;
For the Pope, under the "hospital control", is the rule of the "absolute rest" established by doctors >. That is why yesterday he could not lead - first time - the Marian recitation of the Angelus and the General Audience of Wednesday 19 February was cancelled. Of course, Bergoglio will not attend Sunday Mass on the occasion of the Jubilee of the Diacons.&nbsp; and there are no other changes in his agenda.&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Despite all Francis continues the ordinary administration: today in the usual Bulletin of noon, the name of the reverend&nbsp; Giuseppe Luigi Spiga, of the clergy of the Archdiocese of Cagliari, a&nbsp;vescovo of the Diocese of Grajaú in Brazil. Moreover, the Pope &nbsp; did not want to miss the daily telephone appointment with the parish of the Holy Family of Gaza.> It is the same Romanelli to confirm it on the phone with the Vatican media explaining that in the first days of his shelter "he managed to contact us with a video-call.> He asked us how we were, how it was, he sent us his blessing. The people showed him his closeness, he thanked and gave blessing."
<div </div
&nbsp;
"We heard his voice. It's true, he's tired. He himself said: I have to take care of myself. >But the voice was clear, he listened to us well," said the Argentine priest. Last night, on the other hand, on Sunday, "Papa Francesco sent a written message to my mobile phone", said Father Gabriel. In the people of the Holy Family there was no expectation of a communication with the Pontiff, seen "the news and information of the Holy See on his treatment for bronchitis". Instead Jorge Mario Bergoglio wanted to be present: "He sent me a small message saying that he thanked for his closeness and prayers and returned with his blessing." Prayers that continue incessantly, says Romanelli: "We hope that recovery will take place soon and that it will return to St. Peter to continue his mission and work." &nbsp;
